I wish my successor a better year than the one we had at Farmet.
The euphoria of victory was quickly replaced by the effects of the crisis.
Thanks to the objective sense of the winner Farmet has the worst moments behind him.
The one who came to Slovansky for the first place of the contest for the Firm of the Year organized by Vodaphone last year is Karel Zdarsky the owner of the company Farmet.
The jury rewarded the efforts with which it transformed a tooling workshop in Ceska Skalice into a firm with a turnover of 100 million crowns.
“I can say that the award has encouraged not only me but also my employees and increased our self-confidence to fight against the competition,” said the winner of last year’s competition.
At the beginning of the history of the company Farmet there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state proposed to the father of Karel Zdrasky to rent the small workshop as compensation after the confiscation of goods by the communists, he did not hesitate for a long time, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a company with a few comrades in the entourage of his father in the barn.
Not long after they began to specialize in presses for vegetable oil.
After eighteen years, it became the largest manufacturer of automatic presses in Central Europe.
The company was known even in the non-specialized public after the success achieved in the contest through the media.
“Not only have our customers started to really get to know the Farmet brand better but also foreign partners who have begun to realize that they are working with a company that has achieved the greatest success in its home country,” says Karel Zdarsky.
But the past year did not happen at Farmet only in the euphoria of victory.
The assessment of the company was based on the economic results of 2008 and partly of 2009.
And it was precisely in 2009 that this was the most difficult year for the sale of engineering machinery.
At the height of the crisis, which did not really affect citizens, companies were forced to stop their investment projects and start limiting their purchases of new equipment and technology.
"We have obviously not escaped from this situation."
“The turnover fell by 40 percent, and we had to limit our production and even lay off,” Zdarsky said.
A viable society must know that from time to time unpopular measures must be taken.
But they handled the situation properly and retained beneficial results even though they were lower than they had before the crisis.
However, at Farmet, they continued to invest uncompromisingly in research and development.
“We have built a training and research center with the endowments, strengthened the company’s presentation at international trade fairs and won major awards at national exhibitions,” says Zdarsky.
Everything suggests that the crisis is behind them.
The numbers of affies go up and with them the number of employees as well.
“To the new winner I wish this pleasant feeling of victory but in a calm atmosphere,” says Karel Zdarsky.
The investigation that removes foolish regulations.
The Absurdity of the Year investigation is a part of the business clan for the fourth time.
Some absurd regulations could have been abolished.
This year's infamous winner of the Absurdity of the Year survey was the obligation to bring in the offices documents that officials can obtain online.
More than a third of the 4,000 voters voted for it.
For example, the social affairs administration was asking for a paper extract from the trade register while the grievor can get it in two clicks of the mouse.
It changes thanks to the investigation.
"The Czech Social Insurance Administration will no longer request an extract from the trade register for insurance payment checks," said Jana Buranova, spokesman for the Czech Social Insurance Administration (CSSZ).
To highlight all the regulations and decrees that companies and entrepreneurs must fulfill in the Czech Republic and to remove those that are absurd is the meaning of this competition of the Absurdity of the Year.
This investigation is again this year for the fourth time a part of the business clan organized by Hospodarske noviny and has even greater popularity.
