This year, the government entered into an agreement with bondholders who had refused a previous forced debt restructuring for which Argentina had not settled its dues in 2001.
Now Ms. Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez seems to be edging towards an agreement with creditor governments grouped in the Paris Club, to which it owes some $6.7 billion.
