But last month, Amado Boudou, the Minister of Economy, announced that the Fund would provide “technical assistance” to design a new national consumer price index; which resembles a prelude to INDEC’s sanitation.
It is not clear whether Ms. Fern<0xC3><0xA1>ndez wants to remain in politics beyond the end of her term, now that her husband is no longer by her side.
If she does, she needs to win the support of the middle class, among which Kirchnerism is highly advocated.
When the Argentines return from their summer vacation in March, the wave of sympathy for her will have refluxed.
If she wants to win another election, she will have to decide whether or not to repudiate many of her husband’s policies without noise.
