“The good news is that dogs are doing well,” Whitmore said.
"They're in good shape."
"They have been returned to their rightful owners."
Whitmore refused to say exactly where the dogs had been found, in what neighborhood and under what circumstances they had been found.
"An investigation is underway."
"We don't want to say it," Whitmore said.
"We're following orders."
The owners of the dogs, Kristina Rickard and David Peek, could not be joined to provide a comment Thursday.
They met Wednesday afternoon with their two Akitas at a county animal shelter in Downey.
