The senator could still be exposed to disciplinary action by the Senate Ethics Committee.
Mr. Ensign's lawyers stated that the Department of Justice had "informed that Senator Ensign is no longer the subject of the investigation and that he does not intend to maintain any charges against him in this case."
The Ministry of Justice refrained from commenting on the matter.
